#!/bin/bash
# Claude session picker (physical Ctrl+comma, seen by tmux as M-, — Ghostty maps
# ctrl+, -> Meta+comma), replacing the plugin's list.sh -> picker.sh flow
# (tmux-claude-session-manager).
#
# Why not the plugin's own picker: on enter it attaches the chosen session
# INSIDE the picker popup, so the session inherits the picker's size forever —
# tmux popups can't be resized after creation. That meant jumps never got the
# reading-shaped @claude_popup_width/height the C-. / prefix y popups use.
# Here enter closes the picker popup and re-opens the session in a fresh popup
# at the agent size, on the outer client.
#
# Rows/state icons still come from the plugin (picker.sh --list), so upstream
# stays the source of truth for session state. The alt-, toggle-close bind (the
# same physical Ctrl+comma, via Ghostty's Meta remap — fzf can bind alt-, but not
# ctrl-,) lives in our fzf call now — the plugin clone needs no local patch.
#
# Usage: claude-picker <client_name> <session_name>   tmux binding entry point
#        claude-picker --pick <host_client>           internal: fzf inside the popup
#        claude-picker --attach <host_client> <session>  internal: re-open jump target

SELF="${BASH_SOURCE[0]}"
PLUGIN="$HOME/.tmux/plugins/tmux-claude-session-manager/scripts"

prefix="$(tmux show-option -gqv @claude_session_prefix)"
prefix="${prefix:-claude-}"

# First client NOT attached to an agent session — the outer client that should
# host popups (same heuristic as the plugin's list.sh).
host_client() {
    tmux list-clients -F '#{client_name} #{session_name}' 2>/dev/null |
        awk -v p="$prefix" 'index($2, p) != 1 { print $1; exit }'
}

# Session of a client attached to an agent session — the popup we're inside, if any.
nested_session() {
    tmux list-clients -F '#{client_name} #{session_name}' 2>/dev/null |
        awk -v p="$prefix" 'index($2, p) == 1 { print $2; exit }'
}

case "${1:-}" in

--pick) # runs inside the picker popup
    host="${2:-}"
    export FZF_DEFAULT_OPTS=''
    sel=$("$PLUGIN/picker.sh" --list | fzf --ansi --delimiter='\t' --with-nth=3,4,5 \
        --reverse --cycle --header='Claude sessions · enter: jump · ctrl-x: kill' \
        --preview='tmux capture-pane -ept {2}' --preview-window='right,62%,wrap' \
        --bind='alt-,:abort' \
        --bind="ctrl-x:execute-silent(tmux kill-session -t {2})+reload($PLUGIN/picker.sh --list)")
    [ -z "$sel" ] && exit 0
    target=$(printf '%s' "$sel" | cut -f2)

    # Park the outer client on the session's origin window (best-effort) so
    # the popup opens over where the agent was launched.
    origin=$(tmux show-options -qv -t "$target" @claude_origin 2>/dev/null)
    [ -n "$origin" ] && [ -n "$host" ] && tmux switch-client -c "$host" -t "$origin" 2>/dev/null

    # Opening the session popup from in here would MODIFY this popup (tmux
    # ignores -w/-h on an existing popup) — hand off to the server and exit so
    # the picker popup closes first.
    tmux run-shell -b "'$SELF' --attach '$host' '$target'"
    ;;

--attach) # background: open the jump target at agent size on the outer client
    host="$2" target="$3"
    w="$(tmux show-option -gqv @claude_popup_width)"
    h="$(tmux show-option -gqv @claude_popup_height)"
    sleep 0.1 # let the picker popup finish closing...
    if [ -n "$host" ]; then
        tmux display-popup -C -c "$host" 2>/dev/null # ...or force it
        exec tmux display-popup -c "$host" -w "${w:-90%}" -h "${h:-90%}" \
            -E "tmux attach-session -t '$target'"
    else
        exec tmux display-popup -w "${w:-90%}" -h "${h:-90%}" \
            -E "tmux attach-session -t '$target'"
    fi
    ;;

*) # tmux binding entry point: claude-picker <client_name> <session_name>
    client="${1:-}" session="${2:-}"

    [ -x "$PLUGIN/picker.sh" ] || {
        tmux display-message "claude-picker: tmux-claude-session-manager not installed"
        exit 0
    }
    command -v fzf >/dev/null 2>&1 || {
        tmux display-message "claude-picker: fzf is required"
        exit 0
    }

    if [ -n "$client" ] && [ -n "$session" ] && [[ "$session" != "$prefix"* ]]; then
        host="$client"
    else
        # Invoked from inside the agent popup: close it first — a client can
        # only host one popup, and the picker belongs on the outer client.
        sess="$(nested_session)"
        if [ -n "$sess" ]; then
            tmux detach-client -s "$sess"
            for _ in $(seq 1 100); do
                [ -z "$(nested_session)" ] && break
                sleep 0.05
            done
        fi
        host="$(host_client)"
    fi

    # Wide stock size for the picker (list + 62% preview pane); the
    # reading-shaped @claude_popup_width/height apply only to the session
    # popups themselves (launch.sh and --attach above).
    if [ -n "$host" ]; then
        exec tmux display-popup -c "$host" -w 90% -h 90% -E "'$SELF' --pick '$host'"
    else
        exec tmux display-popup -w 90% -h 90% -E "'$SELF' --pick ''"
    fi
    ;;
esac
